Robert Downey Jr has helped raise more than £1million for British hospice Julia's House  . 
  He promised to fly a winner and a friend to the world premiere of Marvel's Avengers: Age of Ultron . 
  The Ironman actor raised £1,388,863 for the Dorset-based charity . 
  Charity will now use the money to build a new hospice in Wiltshire . 
 